overview: The user started by pointing out an issue with their Vercel dashboard,
  where multiple duplicate projects existed for their "sleep-questionnaire"
  application. I identified the root cause as repeated imports of the same
  GitHub repository and provided instructions on how to clean it up. Upon the
  user's request, I proceeded to delete the four duplicate projects using the
  Vercel CLI, ensuring only the primary project remained. Following this, the
  user inquired about setting up a development environment with a separate
  domain. I outlined several options, ultimately recommending the creation of a
  dedicated  branch, which would allow for branch-specific environment
  variables and the assignment of a custom subdomain for development purposes.
  The user then asked me to proceed with creating this  branch.
